notes: I don't want to get off on a lot of tangents.
Dan: Let's diagnose me.
Adam: You think that I have Asperger's!
Dan on superiority complex: There's a disease called "guy that's awesome?"  Dan wishes he has the skills of the Coen brothers, RoboCop, and Greg Proops.
Dan muses on Happy Days.
Greg Proops to the stage!
Jeff: Hey, everyone, dress up as Jareth from Labyrinth on Halloween!
Dan's docket talk: Apple Friend Finder, and life after death.
Spencer to the stage!  Greg: I want to be with my wife after I die.  Dan: So do I.  Jeff: It's the high five heard around the world!
Dan tells the Schrab story about him misinterpreting the lyrics to Ground Control to Major Tom, thinking "Give my wife my love and nothing more" meant "AND DON'T GIVE HER YOUR DICK!"
Dan tells the Ease the Seat Back/Seed Bag story of the misheard Panama lyrics.
Spencer recaps DND.
Dan calls Thornevail Hawkthorne.  Community reference?
DND end.
"Your car is being towed."  Erin's car gets repossessed.
Dan: Next worse thing to being poor is being rich.  Dan talks about Billy Pilgrim in Slaughterhouse Five.
Dan: Fascism and capitalism are not much different.
The Wave was an equivalent of the Stanford prison experiment.  Dan: We all want not to be excommunicated by each other, but look to each other for what I'm doing wrong.
Are you more happy having money than not?  Dan says $40k is the limit, but poverty is depressing.  What does $40k mean, Dan ponders.

Proops: It's despicable how poor I am considering how awesome I am!  Proops talks about being poor.  "Do I buy this pack of cigarettes, or do I eat?"  Then, the psychopathy of people who have a billion dollars and don't desist.

Dan bought a house with a number value bigger than any house in Milwaukee.  Details magazine did a spread on TV mavericks with him in it, shot in a house worth $82.5MM!  Dan walked through the house thinking, "Aw, fuck, I should have put my toilet on the ceiling."  Greg: Why don't I have an avocado server in the living room?
Jeff felt like a king when he had enough for a burrito and the tip.

When Dan, Jeff, and Rob Schrab met, Jeff was a vagabond, a hobo.  They'd rent movies together.  Jeff once left a note on the coffee table that said, "Tonight I did something I will never forgive myself for.  I took your change from Del Taco because I'm broke.  I promise I will give the money back.  A beautifully written spiel.

Dan made a shitload of money from Monster House and bought Centipede and Pac-Man arcade machines, then three months later he didn't have two nickels to rub together.
More of Jeff's poverty stories.  He had two trash bags of his things and $.45 cents to his name.  He got a role the day he was to be evicted.
Dan starts beatboxing, thinking it's time to close.

Dan: Who in the audience is least happy?  Adam immediately shoots his hand up.  He got fired from his job.  Jeff cuts him off abruptly, but Dan invites him up.  Adam's Valhalla.  Greg: "Is that a hunch, or are you just being a sex monster?"  Adam: "I have a hunch I am a sex monster.  Dan has combed his hair for the very first time on my account."
Adam sings "To Dream the Impossible Dream" to close out the show.
Jeff reminds the audience to reach between their legs and ease the seed bag.
Audience expert on bipolarity.
Greg, then Spencer, to the stage!
